          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "90Zr target of thickness 1.5 mg/cm2, positioned",
                "perpendicular to the beam"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SISD",
                "TELES"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Six dE-E telescope detectors from the",
                "detector array of the EXOTIC facility were used. Each",
                "telescope consisted of two double-sided silicon strip",
                "detectors with thicknesses of 55 and 300 microns. The",
                "telescopes were positioned at different angles around",
                "the target, at a distance of approx. 11 cm. The total",
                "solid angled covered was 1.7 sr. The angular",
                "resolution was estimated to be around 5 degrees."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE",
                "EXTB"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 8Li+90Zr quasi-elastic scattering was",
                "studied at 18.5 and 21.5 MeV (laboratory frame). The",
                "90Zr target was installed in a target ladder at the",
                "center of the scattering chamber. The same ladder also",
                "held a 2 mg/cm2 thick 208Pb target, which was used to",
                "determine the solid angle seen by the detectors."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The 8Li beam was produced as secondary beam by means",
                "of the in-flight technique using the 2H(7Li,8Li)p",
                "reaction. The primary beam with energies of 27 and 29",
                "MeV was directed onto a 5 cm long 2H gas cell, with a",
                "2.2 um thick Havar foil window."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TRCS"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Total reaction cross section were obtained by",
                "optical model analysis using the BDM3Y1 interaction",
                "model."
              ]
            }
          ],
